column5: Well we fish the river hard yesterday morning but no walleye water is still a tade murky but clearing UP quick we found 5 to 7 inches of ice at all our spots we tried yesterday on the main river time to get the Atv out and try so down river spots ...anyways after fishing the river till 10 am we decided to try the Marina for some Crappies and what a good choice ...we fish the steal poles useing small buck shot tiped with a small minnow down around 5 to 7 ft and useing a vex and marcum is a must to catch these picky buggers ...get out and enjoy this great Ice Fishing weather ...
Steve you know where i'll be fishing lol How's the ice?  Might bring the kids for a few hours
Ice is 6 to 7" in the Marina
Some good slabs there for a tasty meal.  Nice!
